beit? Und wer ist für die Dramaturgie in Ausstellungen verantwortlich?Mit Beiträgen u.a. von Lukas Bärfuss, Werner Hanak-Lettner, Herman Kossmann, Nicola Lepp und Frank den Oudsten.  aWhat does dramaturgy mean in exhibition work, and who is responsible for it? A book on theory and practice of exhibition dramaturgy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDramaturgie. 4aKulturelle Bildung. 4aMuseologie. 4aMuseum. 4aMuseumskunde. 4aMuseumsmanagement. 4aMuseumspädagogik. 4aMuseumswissenschaft. 4aNarration. 4aStorytelling. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aCultural Education.  aDramaturgy.  aMuseology.  aMuseum Education.  aMuseum Management.  aMuseum.  aStorytelling.1 aBärfuss, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGesser, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanak-Lettner, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHebeisen, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarbe, Ariane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKossmann, Herman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLepp, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLichtensteiger, Sibylle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMinder, Aline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNoggler-Gürtler, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOudsten, Frank den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStapferhaus Lenzburg, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTonella, Denise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVögeli, Detlef, econtributor.4ctb